The resolver is still seeing stale 4.18 CSV objects internally even after deletion.
This usually happens because the CSVs are stuck in OLM cache/finalizer state.

Now verify whether those CSV objects actually still exist in API:

oc get csv -n openshift-storage -o name

I suspect one of these still exists hidden/stuck:

mcg-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf

odf-prometheus-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf

ocs-client-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf

etc.


If they still appear, force-remove them:

oc patch csv mcg-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
-n openshift-storage \
--type merge \
-p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":[]}}'

Then delete:

oc delete csv mcg-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf -n openshift-storage --force --grace-period=0

Repeat for every remaining 4.18 CSV.

Then clean resolver cache completely:

oc delete pod -n openshift-operator-lifecycle-manager -l app=catalog-operator
oc delete pod -n openshift-operator-lifecycle-manager -l app=olm-operator

Then remove stale installplans again:

oc delete installplan --all -n openshift-storage

After that monitor:

watch -n 5 'oc get csv,installplan -n openshift-storage'

You should finally see:

fresh 4.19 installplans

recreated dependency CSVs

no more ConstraintsNotSatisfiable


The key evidence is this line:

clusterserviceversion odf-prometheus-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf exists

